                     Edward Bullock, Esq., Judge of the Sheriffs' Court; Her Majesty's Justices of Oyer and Terminer, and Gaol Delirery of Newgate, holden for the said City, and Judges of the Central Criminal Court.

861.
EDGAR WHITE was indicted
for wilful and corrupt perjury. (The prosecutor was called on his recognizance, and did not appear.)

868.
SAMUEL HOLT was indicted
for a misdemeanor. (MR. CLARKSON offered no evidence.)
